Aim:- 
To write a Python program to demonstrate different string functions such as upper(), lower(), strip(), replace(), split(), and find().

algorithm:- 
Start the program.
Create a string variable text1 and convert it to uppercase using upper().
Create a string variable text2 and convert it to lowercase using lower().
Create a string with extra spaces and remove them using strip().
Create a string and replace a word using replace().
Create a string containing fruits and split them using split().
Create a string and find the position of a word using find().
Display all the results using print().
Stop the program.

code:-
text1 = "hello"
print("Upper:", text1.upper())
text2 = "PYTHON"
print("Lower:", text2.lower())
text3 = "  hello  "
print("Strip:", text3.strip())
text4 = "I like apples"
print("Replace:", text4.replace("apples", "oranges"))
text5 = "apples, banana, mango"
print("Split:", text5.split(", "))
text6 = "hello world"
print("Find:", text6.find("world"))


output:-
Upper: HELLO
Lower: python
Strip: hello
Replace: I like oranges
Split: ['apples', 'banana', 'mango']
Find: 6
